{
  "texts": [
    "The whole process is recursive, with the original prompt divided into several sub-prompts.",
    "In each iteration, the sub-prompt is compressed into a small set of continuous prompt vectors, which are then passed to the next iteration along with a new sub-prompt for further compression.",
    "This continues until all the encoded embeddings are collected, representing the information from the entire original prompt.",
    "While AutoCompressor increases the maximum prompt length that can be compressed, the training process is time-consuming, and the compression tokens cannot be used by the original untuned LLM.",
    "ICAE increases the compression length and uses the frozen LLM as the decoder (Ge et al., 2024)."
  ]
}